):  I want to take some time going through the government's so-called $100 billion infrastructure program. This is a third-term government, and we are now in its seventh year. I think it is fair to say that the budget this year, in the lead-up to the election, was very much a political document as opposed to an economic plan, seeking—frankly—to paper over the past years of inaction and cuts. It's a government that appears to have two infrastructure ministers but no infrastructure plan—or a plan that is probably based more on an episode of The Hollowmen than on an actual economic development plan.
